@NODE HELPNODE "Getting started"
To  help you in working with Kiskometer, I've pre-installed some commands
here.  Just  click  on  them  using  your  mouse  and the actions will be
performed.

@{"Start Kiskometer" SYSTEM "Run >NIL: Kiskometer CON:0/15/640/100/Kiskometer"}  @{"Start Kiskometer using an Auto-Popup-Window" SYSTEM "Run >NIL: Kiskometer CON:0/15/640/100/Kiskometer/AUTO QUIET"}
@{"Quit Kiskometer" SYSTEM "Kiskometer QUIT"}
@{"Redirect Kiskometer's output to the serial device" SYSTEM "Run >NIL: Kiskometer RAWIO"}
@ENDNODE


@NODE MAIN "Kiskometer - Contents"
Kiskometer  is  a  program  that  checks  which programs use the function
SetFunction()  and  that makes visible which functions have been patched.
You  may  pass a format string and so configure the format of the output.
With  the  help  of  an  extensive  filter you can suppress the output of
specific  calls of SetFunction(). Output occurs to @{I}stdout@{UI}, into a file or
on the serial device - whatever you prefer.

  @{"Copyright" LINK COPYRIGHT}          Only non-commercial distribution allowed
  @{"Disclaimer" LINK DISCLAIMER}         No liability
